oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Performance - Monty Powell and Anna Wilson - 2006-11-07
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Performances by Monty Powell and Anna Wilson for Building Blocks: Habitat for Humanity participants from the Ford Theater at the Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum on November 7, 2006.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Monty Powell; Anna Wilson;
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Program begins in progress. Opening comments by Jay Orr. Introduction of Monty Powell and Anna Wilson. Performances include: Time Changes Everything (Anna Wilson) -- Days Go By (Monty Powell with story about writing the second verse) -- Back In The Day (Anna Wilson) -- Could've Been Me (Monty Powell with story) -- You Don't Know Me (Anna Wilson) -- What A Beautiful Day (Monty Powell) -- Sentimental Sundays (Anna Wilson) -- One Of These Days (Monty Powell) -- A House, A Home (Anna Wilson) -- Who Wouldn't Want To Be Me (Monty Powell and Anna Wilson) -- End.
